Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows markedly elevated serum creatinine, indicating significant renal impairment, and elevated ALT, suggesting possible liver involvement. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal urine appearance, supporting renal dysfunction and possible metabolic derangement (e.g., diabetes or acute illness). Further clinical correlation and nephrology evaluation are recommended.
